==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Traffic mile
<hw>Traf"fic mile</hw>. <fld>(Railroad Accounting)</fld> <def>Any unit
of the total obtained by adding the passenger miles and ton miles in a
railroad's transportation for a given period; -- a term and practice of
restricted or erroneous usage.</def></p>

<p><q><qex>Traffic mile</qex> is a term designed to furnish an excuse
for the erroneous practice of adding together two things (ton miles and
passenger miles) which, being of different kinds, cannot properly be
added.</q> <rj><qau>Hadley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tragacanth</ent>⟦br⟧
